What are Design Patterns?
Design Patterns provide a reusable skeleton for a project, by using which one can create projects more robust and maintainable.

Types of Design Patterns.
The Types of Design Patterns are:
            a. Creational Design Patterns
            b. Structural Design Patterns
            c. Behavioral Design Patterns

Why do we need Design Patterns?
Using Design Patterns will help the project to be more structured and helps to maintain a project more effectively.